    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with tin foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>chopped onion</strong></p><p>Tear your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> roughly into the dish</p><p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> stout paste </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>slow cooked beef brisket </strong>and your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[500ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[650ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 45 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your<strong> beef brisket, stout & mushroom pie mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong>, then drizzle over a large splash of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the potato to form a tightly sealed parcel and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had 20 min, dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong>, roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a rolling pin and cut into rectangles (1 per person!), then score a cross in the middle</p><p>Remove the tray with the potatoes from the oven and add the <strong>pastry rectangle[s]</strong> to the other side, then return the tray to the oven for a final 20-22 min or until the pastry is puffed up and golden \u2013 these are your <strong>cooked potatoes and pie lids</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is ready, transfer the <strong>beef</strong> (keep the sauce in the pan!) to a clean chopping board and pull it apart using two forks \u2013 this is your <strong>pulled beef</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>pulled beef</strong> to the dish with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>beef brisket, stout & mushroom pie mix</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>cooked potato </strong>to a heatproof bowl with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong>, then crush lightly with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>buttery crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-beef-brisket-stout-and-mushroom-pie-with-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>beef brisket, stout & mushroom pie mix </strong>and top with a <strong>pie lid</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> buttery crushed potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
